       State Map

                  Ferry County

                                         Click a number on the map below
                                               for launch details.

                           ferry.gif (86645 bytes)

   Up Arrow to Map   1. Tiffanys Resort

        Waterbody: Curlew Lake
        Site Manager: Tiffanys Resort
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp
                            2 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            None

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Republic, N on SR 21 5.5 mi; L on Curlew Lake Rd .8 mile; R on
        W Curlew Lake Rd 5 mi; R at Tiffanys Resort sign .5 mile to resort
        office; boat ramp is past office to right.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a gentle grade; abrupt edges; upper corner broken.
        To use boat ramp, users must be camping at Tiffanys Park. Boat
        trailer parking is located just before the resort office. No bull
        rails on loading float. Tiffanys Resort also offers rental cabins,
        RV campsites, boat rentals, convenience store, boat moorage,
        swimming area, public phone, and fishing dock.


   Up Arrow to Map   2. Black Beach Resort

        Waterbody: Curlew Lake
        Site Manager: Black Beach Resort
        Nearest City: Republic


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            5 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes, April through October

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Republic, N on SR 21 5.5 mi; L on Curlew Lake Rd; go .8 mi; R
        on W Curlew Lake Rd; go 3 mi; R at Black Beach Resort sign; go .8
        mi; after crossing railroad tracks, continue straight.
        Site Description:

        Boat ramp has gentle grade; accumulates sand; the concrete is in
        good condition; has dropoff 15 feet out. No designated disabled
        parking. Additional parking at resort office. Black Beach Resort
        also offers RV campsites, convenience store, boat rentals, cabin
        rentals, motel rooms, boat moorage, flush restrooms, play equipment,
        and public phone.


   Up Arrow to Map   3. Curlew Lake Boat Launch (Miyoko Point)

        Waterbody: Curlew Lake
        Site Manager:
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Gravel Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            5 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Republic, N on SR 21 approx 5.5 mi; L on Curlew Lake Rd for .8
        mi; R on W. Curlew Lake Rd for 1.8 mi; R on unmarked gravel rd for
        .5 mi to Miyoko Point. Boat ramp is 100 ft past RR tracks on left.
        Site Description:

        Boat ramp has erosion ruts, but has an even surface below the
        shoreline. Ramp has a gentle/moderate grade, but traction may be
        hampered. Parking is informal.


   Up Arrow to Map   4. Fishermans Cove Resort

        Waterbody: Curlew Lake
        Site Manager: Fishermans Cove Resort
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp
                            1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            None

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes, April through October

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Republic, N on SR 21 10 mi; L on Kiwanis Rd; go .5 mi; turn L
        at Fishermans Cove sign; follow gravel Rd to resort.
        Site Description:

        Boat ramp is slightly uneven, has a gentle grade and abrupt edges.
        Sand and gravel accumulate on ramp. No designated disabled parking.
        No charge to use boat ramp. Fishermans Cove Resort also has cabin
        rentals, convenience store, swimming area, boat moorage, RV
        campsites, showers, boat rentals, snack bar, and public phone.


   Up Arrow to Map   5. Pine Point Resort

        Waterbody: Curlew Lake
        Site Manager: Pine Point Resort
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp
                            1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            None

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes, May through October

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Republic, N on SR 21 8 mi; L on Pine Point Rd, go .25 mi to
        resort.
        Site Description:

        Boat ramp has a steep grade, the concrete in good condition, but it
        provides insufficient traction. Visitors must be a registered guest
        of the resort to use boat ramp. Pine Point Resort offers rental
        cabins, convenience store, boat moorage, RV campsites, public phone,
        and restrooms.


   Up Arrow to Map   6. Curlew Lake State Park

        Waterbody: Curlew Lake
        Site Manager: State Parks
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Flush
     Shower
     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Loading Float
                            2 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            10 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Republic, drive 2.5 mi NE on SR 20; n N on SR 21 for 6 mi. boat
        launch is located 1/2 mi from SR 21; take first R past park
        buildings.
        Site Description:

        No disabled parking. Campground has full hook-up sites. Tire are
        located around floats help to prevent damage to boats during loading
        and unloading.


   Up Arrow to Map   7. Davis Lake Campground

        Waterbody: Davis Lake (Ferry Co)
        Site Manager: US Forest Service Portland
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Gravel Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            5 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes, site is closed when snow prevents access.

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Kettle Falls, N on US 395 9 mi; W on Deadman Creek Rd 3.5 mi; N
        on Jacknife Lookout Rd 5 mi; N on Davis Lake Rd 2.5 mi to end of Rd.
        Site Description:

        Ramp has even surface and moderate grade. Davis Lake Campground also
        has vault restrooms and primitive campsites. No designated disabled
        parking.


   Up Arrow to Map   8. Trout Lake Campground

        Waterbody: Trout Lake (Ferry Co)
        Site Manager: US Forest Service Portland
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Gravel Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            4 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes, open as long as roadway is snow-free

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Kettle Falls, N on US 295 3.5 mi; cross FD Roosevelt Lake, turn
        L; follow SR 20, 5.5 mi W; turn R on Trout Lake Rd; go 5 mi.
        Site Description:

        Ramp has gentle grade, with large rocks at toe of ramp. No
        designated disabled parking. The ramp area is shallow, which would
        only accommodate smaller boats. Trout Lake Campground also has
        campsites, vault restrooms, and access to trails.


   Up Arrow to Map   9. Lake Ellen Campground

        Waterbody: Lake Ellen
        Site Manager: US Forest Service Portland
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Gravel Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            5 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Kettle Falls, N on US 395 3.5 mi; at US 395/SR 20 junction,
        veer L & follow SR 20 4.5 mi; L on Inchelum-Kettle Falls Rd 4 mi; R
        on Ellen Lake Rd 4.5 mi; R at Lake Ellen Campground sign; take
        immediate L to get to boat ramp
        Site Description:

        Ramp has even surface and gentle slope. No designated disabled
        parking. Boat ramp area is very shallow, which may prohibit
        launching of larger boats. Lake Ellen Campground also offers vault
        restrooms and campsites.


   Up Arrow to Map   10. French Rocks

        Waterbody: F.D. Roosevelt Lake (Col. River)
        Site Manager: National Park Service
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp
                            1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            17 Paved and Striped Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes, reservoir level may drop below the end of the ramp

        Driving Directions:

        From Kettle Falls, N on US 395 3.5 mi; W on SR 20 4.5 mi; turn L on
        Inchelum-Kettle Falls Rd; go 7 mi; turn L on unmarked Rd; go 300 ft.
        to site.
        Site Description:

        No designated disabled parking. Fee ($6.00) charged to use boat
        ramp. French Rocks also has a beach area and picnic table. No bull
        rails on loading float.


   Up Arrow to Map   11. Rainbow Beach Resort

        Waterbody: North Twin Lake
        Site Manager: Rainbow Beach Resort
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Fuel Available
     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            10 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes, mid-April to mid-October

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Inchelium, W on Bridge Creek Rd 9 mi; turn L on Twin
        Lakes-Strancer Creek Rd; go .5 mi; turn R at Rainbow Beach Resort
        sign.
        Site Description:

        Ramp has broken planks, gentle grade at toe, and uneven surface at
        shoreline. No designated disabled parking. Boat trailer parking is
        at the end of the resort; it is informal parking and quite a walk to
        the boat ramp area. Rainbow Beach Resort offers boat moorage, rental
        cabins, swim area, convenience store, arcade, laundry facilities,
        and boat rentals.


   Up Arrow to Map   12. Hartman's Log Cabin Resort

        Waterbody: South Twin Lake
        Site Manager: Hartmans Log Cabin Resort Inc
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Fuel Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Gravel Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            None

        Seasonal Limitations:

        yes, mid-April to mid-October

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Inchelium, W on Bridge Creek Rd 9 mi; L on Twin Lakes-Strancer
        Creek Rd, go 1.5 mi; turn R at Log Cabin Resort sign.
        Site Description:

        The ramp has steel matting that is warping and may hamper traction;
        has a moderate-steep grade. No designated disabled parking. No bull
        rails on loading float. Log Cabin Resort also has cabin rentals,
        convenience store, laundry facilities, boat rentals, boat moorage,
        RV campsites, motel rooms



